The Telegraph - Calcutta : Business

 Global trade help for Bengal

 Calcutta, Dec. 9 (PTI): The Global Technologies Research of Commonwealth Business Council, a trade promotion body, today offered support to Bengal in the IT sector.

 Council director Mark Kopayashi Hillary said he can offer assistance to the Bengal government to develop the IT initiative in the overseas market.

 Hillary said he will meet the IT minister and discuss how his organisation can offer assistance in the global market.

 He said Calcutta has a huge potential in the software and BPO sectors after Bangalore, which has attained saturation.

 The Global Technologies Research of Commonwealth Business Council is already working on the BPO sector and can also support Bengals thrust in this regard.




